<br>
1) No plans for bard snap aggro. Fine, let's drop that. But it isn't the same as the ability to hold aggro. Not a big one on my list, just pointing that out.<br>
<br>
2) Song fades as it lands, being addressed, but not yet fixed.<br>
<br>
3) Puretone itself won't change. But we could still get an upgrade. We are long overdue an upgrade.<br>
<br>
4) VoVesagran - they are looking into changing the recast.<br>
<br>
So at the moment, none of these four should be removed from the list. Maybe reworded. Possibly its safe to remove #2 and #4 because they said they are working on them, though they might fade from their memories. I would prefer to keep them visiable #1 &amp; #3 should just be reworded to reflect what they haven't yet said no to.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mojojojojoejojo>MojojojoJoejojo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#330000>(6/22/05 4:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=20156.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bard Top 10 Issue List - Starting From Scratch</span><hr size=1> Posted this on the EQLive version of this thread and I'll repost it here for bards who only come to TCH.<br>
<br>
<br>
1) Snare -- I personally agree completly with your assessment that 1+ minute duration detrimental songs, including snare are overpowered for the current definition of bards, but out high end snare has two problems, one you brought up, the resist rate on it is horrible and a solid resist check mod will turn it from a 6 (HoS + Metla) or in some cases 9 (HoS + ACC + Metla) back down to the 3 second song its supposed to be... but the other issue with this song is that it has a random! duration, even when (or if) we get a resist check on the song, it may last less time then it takes to recast.  We deserve to have an 18 second set duration snare which lands on exp mobs of the current expansion (RSS / Nest)<br>
 <br>
2) Shield of Notes -- Rashere said he &quot;fixed&quot; the AA, but from what he actually did to &quot;fix&quot; the song indicates that he had no idea what the original problem was with the AA.  The duration is too short, and the percent migitation does not increase with increasing levels of the AA.  Instead, he increased the total damage the shield can absorb, which does nothing! because given the current durration of the AA coupled with the low, un-scaling, percentage migitation means that bards almost never! use up the absorbable damage of level 1, making ranks 2 and 3 completly useless.  Further feedback on the problems of this AA can be found here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&message.id=3894">eqforums.station.sony.com...ge.id=3894</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
 <br>
3) Kessdona's Roar (Speaker of the Scale click) -- The community really could use feedback on this click.  The damage dealt is the second lowest of all clicks, the resist check tied for the worst, the range is the second lowest, and the recast is TWICE the second highest recast.  The click needs a FULL re-evaluation and needs to be brought into line with all other class clicks.  Rogue vish item has already! recieved attention and a pending fix by Zajeer, and our community has been asking for a tune for weeks and weeks before thiers was. (Ever since the REAL click was deemed too hard to code).  Further feedback on the problems of this AA can be found here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=bardbalance&message.id=4294">eqforums.station.sony.com...ge.id=4294</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
 <br>
4) Jaxans Jig of Vigor -- understandably this song does not function with current  endurance system, but bards have always been partially defined by our 1 song-per-level, as well as a general trend by the devs to get every class at least 1 spell-per-level... what has been done to replace Jaxans Jig with a level 3 song that does have functionality.<br>
 <br>
5) Ardent Renewal / Staunch Recovery -- In the fan fare report, you mentioned this was going to recieve some possible attention.  This might be worth adding to the queue for our 10th slot.<br>
<br>
6) Lockpick -- Personally, I'm extreemly annoyed at needing a level 50 rogue to be able to open the crypt in Sebilis, or the exit from Vernil Sathir, or the door to the Chardok Royals... from 5 and 6 year old expansions without having to be summoned accross.  And yet, I still carry my mechanized lockpicks and gloves of the brood wherever I go... This is a very old problem that recieved limited attention in the form of changing how picklock and disarm trap encounters work in LDoN+, however the change did not remove the problems that already existed.  Please consider giving bards an AA which would allow picklock skill to increase to 200.  Perhaps make it cost 18 AA, and put it in place of our very useless Spell Casting Subtlety of the same cost.<br>
<br>
7) Total lack of creativity with new bard songs! Nearly our entire OoW song set was nothing more then a scaled up PoP song set which completly goes against how the bard is set up for the first 60 levels where most songs along our level curve are completly original, and scale up as we level, I would just like some sort of commitment from developers that they plan to keep some level of creativity in the future bard spell lines rather then giving us the same 10 songs every expansion.<br>
